---
import Docs from "../../../layouts/Docs.astro";

const dirs = [
  { name: "architecture.md", role: "convention", here: "The system's shape — core areas, and the orientation an agent reads first.", write: "One or two paragraphs. What this system is and any guidance before touching code.", not: "Not feature detail (that's a spec) and not history (that's knowledge/archive)." },
  { name: "conventions/", role: "convention", here: "Doc and code standards, templates, the graduation prompt.", write: "Standards the whole repo follows. Stable, rarely changing.", not: "Not the repo's pins/thresholds — those live in specline.yml at the root, not here." },
  { name: "decisions/", role: "convention", here: "Repo-local ADRs — one per decision, append-only once accepted.", write: "A decision and its rationale. ADR > spec > knowledge in precedence.", not: "Not a plan (spec) and not a description of what exists (knowledge)." },
  { name: "strategy/", role: "convention", here: "Vision, roadmap snapshots, launch contracts. Dated; archived, not deleted.", write: "Where the product is going. Point-in-time, so date it.", not: "Not how a feature works — that's knowledge." },
  { name: "technical/", role: "convention", here: "Cross-cutting implementation patterns that span features.", write: "Only when a pattern is non-obvious and reused across specs.", not: "Not per-feature mechanics (that's the code, or a spec's design.md)." },
  { name: "specs/", role: "enforced", here: "IN-FLIGHT work. One folder per feature being shaped or built.", write: "Prescriptive — what we intend to build. Temporary by design.", not: "Not shipped reality. The moment it ships it graduates out of here." },
  { name: "knowledge/", role: "enforced", here: "SHIPPED reality. The living, present-tense description of what's true now.", write: "Intent, rules, rationale — what the code can't say. Cut anything the code already says.", not: "No lifecycle files (status.md, open-questions.md) — this isn't in-flight work." },
  { name: "archive/", role: "enforced", here: "TERMINAL contracts. The final spec of every shipped/killed feature, frozen.", write: "Nothing by hand — graduation writes it. Read-only, permanent.", not: "Never edited. It's the audit trail; editing it is a Specline error." },
];
---
<Docs title="Reference — the docs/ layout">
  <div class="doc-kicker">Reference · Layout</div>
  <h1>The <code>docs/</code> layout</h1>
  <p class="doc-lead">
    Specline defines <code>docs/</code> as the product's source of truth — the prescriptive
    record it's built <em>from</em> and the descriptive memory of what it became. Each
    directory has one job. Specline <strong>enforces</strong> the lifecycle core
    (<code>specs/</code>, <code>knowledge/</code>, <code>archive/</code>); the rest are
    <strong>conventions</strong> the canon defines and you maintain.
  </p>
  <p>Knowing which directory a thing belongs in — and which it does <em>not</em> — is the difference between a rule and a habit:</p>
  {dirs.map((d) => (
    <div class="bcard">
      <h3><code>{d.name}</code> <span class="gate-tag" class:list={[d.role === "enforced" ? "gate-doctor" : "gate-human"]}>{d.role === "enforced" ? "Specline · enforced" : "convention"}</span></h3>
      <p><strong>What's here.</strong> {d.here}</p>
      <p><strong>How to write it.</strong> {d.write}</p>
      <p><strong>What's not here.</strong> {d.not}</p>
    </div>
  ))}
  <p>Two generated files round it out: <code>relations-index.yml</code> (reverse-edge index, regenerated by Specline — never hand-edited) and a <code>README.md</code> in each directory carrying this same four-part definition, so the structure explains itself in place.</p>
  <div class="callout"><span class="ci">▸</span><p>Up: <a href="/handbook/specs-in-the-codebase">handbook — the spec lives in the codebase</a>. The law: <a href="/spec.md">the canon, "Repository layout"</a>.</p></div>
</Docs>
